This paper is about automated machine learning (AutoML), which involves using algorithms to automatically build and optimize machine learning models. The paper discusses a benchmark framework for comparing different AutoML systems, which involves evaluating their performance on a set of public datasets. This work is likely to be of interest to researchers in several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE).
